---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import AnimatedCard from "../../components/AnimatedCard.jsx";
---

<MainLayout title="About GBS">
  <AnimatedCard client:load>
    <div
      class="m-4 md:m-12 p-6 md:p-10 bg-white rounded-xl max-w-4xl w-full mx-auto text-gray-800 font-sans bg-opacity-70"
    >
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          What is Guillain-Barré Syndrome?
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Understanding the condition behind the challenge.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto my-12 px-4">
        <a
          href="/gbs-info.png"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          aria-label="Open full-size GBS infographic in a new tab"
          title="Click to view full size"
        >
          <img
            src="/gbs-info.png"
            alt="An infographic summarizing key facts about Guillain-Barré Syndrome, including its rarity (1-2 in 100,000), cause (autoimmune), and recovery statistics (~85% recover well, ~15% have long-term effects)."
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-xl cursor-pointer"
          />
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-16 gap-y-12">
        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">
              What is Guillain-Barré Syndrome?
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Guillain-Barré Syndrome (GBS) is a rare and serious autoimmune
                disorder where the body's immune system mistakenly attacks its
                own peripheral nerves—the network outside of the brain and
                spinal cord.
              </p>
              <p>
                The onset is often sudden, escalating over hours or days into a
                neurological emergency. It is the leading cause of acute,
                non-trauma-related paralysis worldwide.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">
              A Case of Mistaken Identity
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                The most accepted theory is <strong
                  class="font-semibold text-gray-900"
                  >"molecular mimicry"</strong
                >. Often, the syndrome begins after a common infection, like a
                stomach bug (*Campylobacter jejuni*) or a respiratory virus.
              </p>
              <p>
                The immune system creates antibodies to fight the germ, but some
                parts of the germ look remarkably similar to our own nerve
                cells. The antibodies make a catastrophic error and begin
                attacking the healthy nerves, leading to the weakness, numbness,
                and paralysis that define GBS.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">
              Hope on the Horizon
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              While current treatments help, they are not a cure and are not
              effective for everyone. This is why research is so critical.
              Scientists are working to find faster diagnostic tools and develop
              new, more targeted therapies. Your support helps fuel this vital
              research and brings hope to every person affected by GBS.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">
              A Rapidly Escalating Emergency
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Symptoms often begin with tingling in the feet and hands, quickly
              followed by muscle weakness that spreads upwards over hours or
              days. At its most severe, GBS can be devastating:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-6 w-6 text-red-500"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <p class="ml-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900"
                    >Respiratory Failure:</strong
                  > Up to one-third of patients require a mechanical ventilator in
                  an ICU to survive.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-6 w-6 text-red-500"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <p class="ml-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900"
                    >Severe Pain & Paralysis:</strong
                  > Many patients experience near-total paralysis and debilitating
                  nerve pain.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">
              The Long Road to Recovery
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Recovery from GBS is a marathon. While most people learn to walk
              again, the process can take months or even years, and many
              survivors are left with life-altering residual issues, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-6 w-6 text-blue-500"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <p class="ml-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
                  Chronic Neuropathic Pain
                </p>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-6 w-6 text-blue-500"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <p class="ml-3 text-lg text-gray-600">Debilitating Fatigue</p>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg
                    class="h-6 w-6 text-blue-500"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <p class="ml-3 text-lg text-gray-600">
                  Lingering Weakness and Numbness
                </p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <img
          src="/gbs-details.png"
          alt="Guillain-Barré Syndrome Explanation - Neuron and Nerve System"
          class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full object-cover"
        />
        <p class="mt-4 text-center text-sm text-gray-500">
          *Image illustrating the impact of GBS on nerve cells and pathways.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-16 border-gray-200 w-48 mx-auto" />

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Find Out More</h3>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div
            class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 flex flex-col text-center"
          >
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">
              GBS|CIDP Foundation Int.
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2 flex-grow text-sm">
              The leading global nonprofit for supporting patients and funding
              research for GBS.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://www.gbs-cidp.org/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="mt-4 inline-block text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline"
              >Visit Website &rarr;</a
            >
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 flex flex-col text-center"
          >
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">GBS|CIDP España</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2 flex-grow text-sm">
              A patient advocacy group based in Spain, providing support and
              resources.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://gbs-cidp.org.es/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline"
              >Visit Website &rarr;</a
            >
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6 flex flex-col text-center"
          >
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">NINDS (USA)</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2 flex-grow text-sm">
              Provides reliable, in-depth medical information on GBS from the
              U.S. National Institutes of Health.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://www.ninds.nih.gov/health-information/disorders/guillain-barre-syndrome"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline"
              >Visit Information Page &rarr;</a
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </AnimatedCard>
</MainLayout>
